			</div><div class="blogs_commententrybody">
				This was my first gut reaction to the situation when we learned=
 that a relative of the head hancho was involved=2E  My husband=
 also reads this blog, and he and I discussed it=2E  It seems like=
 family politics to me=2E

Jonathan obviously knows his brother is up to no good - he seems=
 to know everything before the Chief even gets his mouth open to=
 explain it=2E  Yet he hasn't fired his brother yet=2E=2E=2E why?  Well,=
 that's easy=2E  He doesn't want to be the bad guy in the family=2E =
 I'm guessing that this is a younger brother - probably someone=
 the rest of his family pressured him into hiring, give him a=
 chance and all that=2E  Jonathan can't fire him, even though he=
 knows what's going on, without risking bringing down his=
 family's ire=2E  However, if someone from outside the company were=
 to discover what was going on (enter Chief) he would then be=
 "forced" to report the situation to the police and fire the=
 offenders=2E  He could then tell his family with a clear concience=
 that he did everything he could to spare his brother the=
 situation, but that it had been taken out of his hands when=
 someone else found out about it=2E

This is one reason why it's usually not a good idea to work with=
 family=2E  Not only do you have to deal with the everyday crap at=
 the watercooler with them, but if anything happens between you=
 at the office, it then gets dragged into your personal life as=
 well=2E

I can't wait to see the conclusion to see if I'm right or not=2E=2E=2E=
 Hopefully I won't look completely silly=2E *blush*


